      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "While this Answer is correct technically, note that the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/package-summary.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">java.time</a> classes supplant the troublesome old date-time classes such as <code>java.util.Date</code>. The old classes are legacy and should be avoided. While you can indeed convert to/from the legacy and java.time classes, it is best to stick with java.time whenever possible."
